Citation.sAbstract: The heat capacity of tetrakis(2,2,6,6-tetramethyl-3,5-heptanedionato)zirconium (Zr(C11H19O2)4) was measured over the temperature range (9-306) K by adiabatic-shield calorimetry and found to be without transitions or thermal anomalies. The data obtained were used to calculate its thermodynamic functions (entropy, enthalpy, reduced Gibbs energy) in the range (0-306) K. They have the following values at 298.15 K: Cp = (1195.7 +- 1.8) J K-1 mol-1, D0,298.15Sm = (1298 +- 3) J K-1 mol-1, D0,298.15Hm = (194.7 +- 0.3) kJ mol-1, Fm = (645.2 +- 1.9) J K-1 mol-1. The value of the absolute entropy were used to calculate the entropy of formation of Zr(C11H19O2)4 at T = 298.15 K.
